nique value. If special values or problems are encountered, the department may modify buffer zone requirements.</p><p><strong>Final Deficiency:</strong> This is the final deficiency (Bobs version) for this rule.</p></div></td></tr>
				<tr class="ParentRule" style="background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);"><td><span class="comply" title="Complies" style="margin-left: 1.7em; padding: 6px 13px;"></span></td><td class="SectionNumber" style="white-space: nowrap;">17.24.519</td><td>Monitoring for Settlement                    </td><td style="white-space: nowrap;">Inspector names</td><td style="text-align: center;"><button onclick="ToggleChildren(this, &quot;17.24.519&quot;)" value="Submit" class="Open" style="background-color: #f9f9f9; padding: 2px 8px; border: solid 3px #eee;" title="Deficiency">+</button></td></tr><tr class="ChildRule Collapsed" data-section="17.24.519"><td style="padding: 0;"><button value="Submit" class="ShowComments Expander" title="Deficiency" style="background-color: #f9f9f9;"><span class="comply" title="Complies" style="padding: 6px 0px; padding-right: 24px; margin: 0em;"></span>&nbsp;▼</button></td><td>519(1)</td><td><div class="text-content short-text">The department may require the operator to monitor settling of regraded areas. The results of these studies may be used to alter reclamation, spoiling and grading techniques to alleviate uneven settling problems on future areas to be mined.</div><div class="show-more"><a href="#">Show more</a></div></td><td>Inspector names</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr class="Definition Collapsed" style="background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);"><td colspan="5" style="margin:0; padding:0;"><div class="Comments" style="padding: 0em 2em; border: solid #F26522 1px; border-radius: 0; background-color: #ffffff;display:none;"><p><strong>Rule:</strong> The department may require the operator to monitor settling of regraded areas. The results of these studies may be used to alter reclamation, spoiling and grading techniques to alleviate uneven settling problems on future areas to be mined.</p><p><strong>Final Deficiency:</strong> This is the final deficiency (Bobs version) for this rule.</p></div></td></tr>
