				<tr class="ChildRule Collapsed" data-section="17.24.927"><td style="padding: 0;"><button value="Submit" class="ShowComments Expander" title="Deficiency" style="background-color: #f9f9f9;"><span class="comply" title="Complies" style="padding: 6px 0px; padding-right: 24px; margin: 0em;"></span>&nbsp;▼</button></td><td>927(3)</td><td><div class="text-content short-text">The design of the durable rock fill must include an internal drainage system, in accordance with ARM 17.24.924(14), that will ensure continued free drainage of anticipated seepage from precipitation and from springs or wet-weather seeps.</div><div class="show-more"><a href="#">Show more</a></div></td><td>Inspector names</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr class="Definition Collapsed" style="background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);"><td colspan="5" style="margin:0; padding:0;"><div class="Comments" style="padding: 0em 2em; border: solid #F26522 1px; border-radius: 0; background-color: #ffffff;display:none;"><p><strong>Rule:</strong> The design of the durable rock fill must include an internal drainage system, in accordance with ARM 17.24.924(14), that will ensure continued free drainage of anticipated seepage from precipitation and from springs or wet-weather seeps.</p><p><strong>Final Deficiency:</strong> This is the final deficiency (Bobs version) for this rule.</p></div></td></tr>
				<tr class="ChildRule Collapsed" data-section="17.24.927"><td style="padding: 0;"><button value="Submit" class="ShowComments Expander" title="Deficiency" style="background-color: #f9f9f9;"><span class="comply" title="Complies" style="padding: 6px 0px; padding-right: 24px; margin: 0em;"></span>&nbsp;▼</button></td><td>927(3)(a)</td><td><div class="text-content short-text">Anticipated discharge from springs and seeps must be based on records and/or field investigations to determine seasonal variation. The design of the internal drainage system must be based on the maximum anticipated discharge.</div><div class="show-more"><a href="#">Show more</a></div></td><td>Inspector names</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr class="Definition Collapsed" style="background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);"><td colspan="5" style="margin:0; padding:0;"><div class="Comments" style="padding: 0em 2em; border: solid #F26522 1px; border-radius: 0; background-color: #ffffff;display:none;"><p><strong>Rule:</strong> Anticipated discharge from springs and seeps must be based on records and/or field investigations to determine seasonal variation. The design of the internal drainage system must be based on the maximum anticipated discharge.</p><p><strong>Final Deficiency:</strong> This is the final deficiency (Bobs version) for this rule.</p></div></td></tr>
				<tr class="ChildRule Collapsed" data-section="17.24.927"><td style="padding: 0;"><button value="Submit" class="ShowComments Expander" title="Deficiency" style="background-color: #f9f9f9;"><span class="comply" title="Complies" style="padding: 6px 0px; padding-right: 24px; margin: 0em;"></span>&nbsp;▼</button></td><td>927(3)(b)</td><td><div class="text-content short-text">All granular material used for the drainage system must be free of clay and consist of durable particles such as natural sands and gravels, sandstone, limestone, or other durable rock that do not slake in water.</div><div class="show-more"><a href="#">Show more</a></div></td><td>Inspector names</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr class="Definition Collapsed" style="background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);"><td colspan="5" style="margin:0; padding:0;"><div class="Comments" style="padding: 0em 2em; border: solid #F26522 1px; border-radius: 0; background-color: #ffffff;display:none;"><p><strong>Rule:</strong> All granular material used for the drainage system must be free of clay and consist of durable particles such as natural sands and gravels, sandstone, limestone, or other durable rock that do not slake in water.</p><p><strong>Final Deficiency:</strong> This is the final deficiency (Bobs version) for this rule.</p></div></td></tr>
				<tr class="ChildRule Collapsed" data-section="17.24.927"><td style="padding: 0;"><button value="Submit" class="ShowComments Expander" title="Deficiency" style="background-color: #f9f9f9;"><span class="comply" title="Complies" style="padding: 6px 0px; padding-right: 24px; margin: 0em;"></span>&nbsp;▼</button></td><td>927(3)(c)</td><td><div class="text-content short-text">The internal drain system must be protected by a properly designed filter system.</div><div class="show-more"><a href="#">Show more</a></div></td><td>Inspector names</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr class="Definition Collapsed" style="background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);"><td colspan="5" style="margin:0; padding:0;"><div class="Comments" style="padding: 0em 2em; border: solid #F26522 1px; border-radius: 0; background-color: #ffffff;display:none;"><p><strong>Rule:</strong> The internal drain system must be protected by a properly designed filter system.</p><p><strong>Final Deficiency:</strong> This is the final deficiency (Bobs version) for this rule.</p></div></td></tr>
				<tr class="ChildRule Collapsed" data-section="17.24.927"><td style="padding: 0;"><button value="Submit" class="ShowComments Expander" title="Deficiency" style="background-color: #f9f9f9;"><span class="comply" title="Complies" style="padding: 6px 0px; padding-right: 24px; margin: 0em;"></span>&nbsp;▼</button></td><td>927(4)</td><td><div class="text-content short-text">Surface water runoff from the areas adjacent to and above the fill must not be allowed to flow into the fill and must be diverted into stabilized channels that are designed to pass safely the runoff from a 100-year, six-hour precipitation event. Diversion design must comply with the requirements of ARM 17.24.637.</div><div class="show-more"><a href="#">Show more</a></div></td><td>Inspector names</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr class="Definition Collapsed" style="background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);"><td colspan="5" style="margin:0; padding:0;"><div class="Comments" style="padding: 0em 2em; border: solid #F26522 1px; border-radius: 0; background-color: #ffffff;display:none;"><p><strong>Rule:</strong> Surface water runoff from the areas adjacent to and above the fill must not be allowed to flow into the fill and must be diverted into stabilized channels that are designed to pass safely the runoff from a 100-year, six-hour precipitation event. Diversion design must comply with the requirements of ARM 17.24.637.</p><p><strong>Final Deficiency:</strong> This is the final deficiency (Bobs version) for this rule.</p></div></td></tr>
				<tr class="ChildRule Collapsed" data-section="17.24.927"><td style="padding: 0;"><button value="Submit" class="ShowComments Expander" title="Deficiency" style="background-color: #f9f9f9;"><span class="comply" title="Complies" style="padding: 6px 0px; padding-right: 24px; margin: 0em;"></span>&nbsp;▼</button></td><td>927(5)</td><td><div class="text-content short-text">The top surface of the completed fill must be graded such that the final slope after settlement will be no steeper than 1v:5h, unless otherwise approved in writing by the department, toward properly designed drainage channels constructed in undisturbed ground along the periphery of the fill. Surface runoff from the top of the fill must not be allowed to flow over the outslope of the fill.</div><div class="show-more"><a href="#">Show more</a></div></td><td>Inspector names</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr class="Definition Collapsed" style="background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);"><td colspan="5" style="margin:0; padding:0;"><div class="Comments" style="padding: 0em 2em; border: solid #F26522 1px; border-radius: 0; background-color: #ffffff;display:none;"><p><strong>Rule:</strong> The top surface of the completed fill must be graded such that the final slope after settlement will be no steeper than 1v:5h, unless otherwise approved in writing by the department, toward properly designed drainage channels constructed in undisturbed ground along the periphery of the fill. Surface runoff from the top of the fill must not be allowed to flow over the outslope of the fill.</p><p><strong>Final Deficiency:</strong> This is the final deficiency (Bobs version) for this rule.</p></div></td></tr>
				<tr class="ChildRule Collapsed" data-section="17.24.927"><td style="padding: 0;"><button value="Submit" class="ShowComments Expander" title="Deficiency" style="background-color: #f9f9f9;"><span class="comply" title="Complies" style="padding: 6px 0px; padding-right: 24px; margin: 0em;"></span>&nbsp;▼</button></td><td>927(6)</td><td><div class="text-content short-text">Surface runoff from the outslope of the fill must be diverted off the fill to properly designed channels that will pass safely a 100-year, six-hour precipitation event. Diversion design must comply with the requirements of ARM 17.24.637.</div><div class="show-more"><a href="#">Show more</a></div></td><td>Inspector names</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr class="Definition Collapsed" style="background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);"><td colspan="5" style="margin:0; padding:0;"><div class="Comments" style="padding: 0em 2em; border: solid #F26522 1px; border-radius: 0; background-color: #ffffff;display:none;"><p><strong>Rule:</strong> Surface runoff from the outslope of the fill must be diverted off the fill to properly designed channels that will pass safely a 100-year, six-hour precipitation event. Diversion design must comply with the requirements of ARM 17.24.637.</p><p><strong>Final Deficiency:</strong> This is the final deficiency (Bobs version) for this rule.</p></div></td></tr>
				<tr class="ChildRule Collapsed" data-section="17.24.927"><td style="padding: 0;"><button value="Submit" class="ShowComments Expander" title="Deficiency" style="background-color: #f9f9f9;"><span class="comply" title="Complies" style="padding: 6px 0px; padding-right: 24px; margin: 0em;"></span>&nbsp;▼</button></td><td>927(7)</td><td><div class="text-content short-text">Terraces must be constructed on the outslope if necessary for control of erosion. Terraces must meet the following requirements:</div><div class="show-more"><a href="#">Show more</a></div></td><td>Inspector names</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr class="Definition Collapsed" style="background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);"><td colspan="5" style="margin:0; padding:0;"><div class="Comments" style="padding: 0em 2em; border: solid #F26522 1px; border-radius: 0; background-color: #ffffff;display:none;"><p><strong>Rule:</strong> Terraces must be constructed on the outslope if necessary for control of erosion. Terraces must meet the following requirements:</p><p><strong>Final Deficiency:</strong> This is the final deficiency (Bobs version) for this rule.</p></div></td></tr>
				<tr class="ChildRule Collapsed" data-section="17.24.927"><td style="padding: 0;"><button value="Submit" class="ShowComments Expander" title="Deficiency" style="background-color: #f9f9f9;"><span class="comply" title="Complies" style="padding: 6px 0px; padding-right: 24px; margin: 0em;"></span>&nbsp;▼</button></td><td>927(7)(a)</td><td><div class="text-content short-text">The slope of the outslope between terrace benches must not exceed 1v:3h, unless otherwise approved in writing by the department.</div><div class="show-more"><a href="#">Show more</a></div></td><td>Inspector names</td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><tr class="Definition Collapsed" style="background-color: rgb(243, 243, 243);"><td colspan="5" style="margin:0; padding:0;"><div class="Comments" style="padding: 0em 2em; border: solid #F26522 1px; border-radius: 0; background-color: #ffffff;display:none;"><p><strong>Rule:</strong> The slope of the outslope between terrace benches must not exceed 1v:3h, unless otherwise approved in writing by the department.</p><p><strong>Final Deficiency:</strong> This is the final deficiency (Bobs version) for this rule.</p></div></td></tr>
